From 558f16446b7a6ed299ed82b01b10471e0508d7a5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Jun 2025 17:55:30 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:wifi:ath12k: Enhance 6 GHz Channel List
 Setup
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Currently, during mac80211 registration, the ath12k driver initializes
the bands in the wiphy object. It allocates channel lists for the 9 power
modes and sets the legacy channel list, which is power mode agnostic
to point to the first power mode list, which corresponds to the LPI mode.

This has a problem where the agnostic list becomes invalid in scenarios
such as outdoor deployments where LPI is not permitted, and in regulatory
domains where each power mode may have a distinct set of allowed channels.

To address this issue, allocate a separate power mode agnostic channel
list for the 6 GHz band (similar to 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz bands) and populate
it as a superset of all power mode-specific channel lists during
regulatory domain updates in cfg80211.

This ensures correctness and scalability across different regulatory
deployments / configurations. Additionally, disable channels outside
the hardware-supported range in the newly allocated list. For split-band
radios within the same hardware group, intersect the new band’s channel
list with the existing band channel lists to maintain consistency.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
subsys/0048-cfg80211-mac80211-regulatory-awgn-and-6g-channel-cha.patch
subsys/0301-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-cfg80211-Enhance-6GHz-Channel-List.patch

